{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2018}}
{{Use Indian English|date=April 2018}}
[[File:Magnetic Hill, Leh.jpg|thumb|300px|Magnetic Hill in [[Ladakh]], India.]]
[[File:Magnetic Hill (India) sign.jpg|thumbnail|A sign near the Magnetic Hill in Ladakh, India.]]
'''Magnet Hill''' is a "Cyclops [[gravity hill|hill]]" located near [[Leh|Leh]] in [[Ladakh]], [[India]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eureka4you.com/magnetichillworldwide/Leh-JK.htm|title=Magnetic Hill Leh, Jammu & Kashmir|access-date=6 March 2016}}</ref> The layout of the area and surrounding slopes create the appearance of a hill. The hill road is actually a downhill road. Objects and cars on the hill road may appear to roll uphill in defiance of gravity when they are, in fact, rolling downhill.<ref>{{cite news|title=NOTHING MAGNETIC ABOUT MAGNETIC HILL|url=http://www.bangaloremirror.com/others/sci-tech/Nothing-magnetic-about-Magnetic-Hill/articleshow/48299466.cms|date=31 July 2015|access-date=11 March 2016}}</ref>

The other two such magnetic hills are in [[Gujarat]]. One is near [[Bhuj]] ([[Kalo Dungar|Kalo dungar]] - the black hills) and other at [[Tulsishyam|Tulsi Shyam]].

