==Provenance and exhibition==
The [[National Gallery of Canada]] purchased the painting from Thomson in 1915 for $500 ({{Inflation|CA|500|1914|fmt=eq|r=-3|cursign=[[Canadian Dollar|CAD$]]}}),{{sfnb|Silcox|2006|p=209}}{{sfnb|Silcox|2015|p=[https://www.aci-iac.ca/art-books/tom-thomson/biography/#a-startling-debut 13], [https://www.aci-iac.ca/art-books/tom-thomson/significance-and-critical-issues/#thomson-and-the-art-market 65]}} essentially a years wage for a painter like himself.{{sfnb|Silcox|2015|p=[https://www.aci-iac.ca/art-books/tom-thomson/key-works/northern-river 26]}} Since then, it has appeared in over 30 exhibitions, including shows at [[Galerie nationale du Jeu de Paume|Musée & du Jeu de Paume]] in [[Paris]]; [[Los Angeles]]; [[London]]; and [[Mexico]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Northern River, Winter 1914–15 (1914–1915.11)|url=http://tomthomsoncatalogue.org/catalogue/entry.php?id=278|website=tomthomsoncatalogue.org|publisher=Tom Thomson Catalgoue}}</ref>

