{{italic title}} '''''The Game and Playe of Chesse''''' is a book by [[William Caxton]], the first English printer. Published in the 1470s, it was for a time thought to be the first book published in English but that title now goes to ''[[Recuyell of the Historyes of Troye]]'', also by Caxton. It was based on a book by [[Jacobus de Cessolis]].<ref>Knowles, Christine. [https://www.jstor.org/pss/3719592 "Caxton and His Two French Sources: The 'Game and Playe of the Chesse' and the Composite Manuscripts of the Two French Translations of the 'Ludus Scaccorum'"] {{subscription required}}. ''[[Modern Language Review]]'' '''49''' (4): 417–423. October 1954. Hosted by [[JSTOR]].</ref> The book is an "allegory of fixed social structures where each rank has its allotted role."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bl.uk/treasures/caxton/firstbook.html|title=Caxton's Chaucer}}</ref>
